A stray dog who lost his nose after he accidentally caught it in a snare could soon be able to smell again thanks to surgeons who are planning to insert a specially designed implant into his snout.

Parys, from Bialystok, Poland, will undergo surgery tomorrow in order to receive his new nose, which was designed by Polish company Ledo.

The tube shaped implant - which was specially built for Parys following a CT scan - was invented by Dr Marcin Elgal from the Individual Medical Implants Technopark, after he heard of the dog's plight.

